## Key Architectural Patterns

### 1. **RAG-as-a-Tool Pattern**
- Ingestion pipeline runs independently (scheduled or manual)
- Retrieval exposed as **LangChain Tool** (`VectorStoreTool`)
- Any agent can use Pinecone via tool interface — no direct coupling

### 2. **Namespace Segregation**
- Logical separation of knowledge domains
- Prevents cross-contamination (marketing queries don't return HR policies)
- Easy to add new domains: create namespace + ingest pipeline

### 3. **Multiple Retrieval Interfaces**
| Interface | Trigger | Use Case |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| Voice RAG | Webhook (POST) | Voice assistants, phone systems, async queries |
| Chatbot | Chat Trigger | Slack/Teams bots, web chat, internal helpdesk |
| Think Agent | Tool Call | Multi-tool agent needing knowledge lookup |

### 4. **Embedding Consistency**
- Single embedding model (`text-embedding-3-small`) for all namespaces
- Ensures vector space compatibility
- Easy to migrate: re-embed all namespaces with new model

---

## Scaling Considerations

| Aspect | Current | Scaling Path |
|--------|---------|--------------|
| **Vector Count** | ~10K vectors | Pinecone scales to billions |
| **Query Latency** | ~200-500ms | Increase pod size / replicas |
| **Namespaces** | 3 | Add per-department / per-project |
| **Embedding Model** | text-embedding-3-small | Upgrade to 3-large for accuracy |
| **Chunk Strategy** | Recursive (fixed) | Semantic chunking for better retrieval |